'''Saleh Hardani''' ({{langx|fa|صالح حردانی}}; born 26 December 1998), also known as '''Saadat Hardani''', is an Iranian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for the [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] club [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|saleh-hardani/627913}}</ref> He is younger brother of [[Saber Hardani]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1621832 |title=حردانی: برادرم به تیم اول فولاد آمد و پاس گل داد}}</ref>

==Club career==

=== Foolad ===
He made his debut for [[Foolad F.C.|Foolad]] in first fixtures of [[2019–20 Iran Pro League]] against [[Sanat Naft Abadan F.C.|Sanat Naft Abadan]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1631893 |title=فولاد 0 - صنعت نفت 1؛ انتقام اسکوچیچ از فولادِ نکونام}}</ref>

=== Esteghlal ===
He joined [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] for [[2021–22 Persian Gulf Pro League|2019–20 Iran Pro League]] and scored an important goal against his previous club, [[Foolad F.C.|Foolad]], which made [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] the champion of the season.

==Personal life==
On 4 February 2026, Hardani responded to the [[2025–2026 Iranian protests]] and the government's crackdown of the protests on his [[Instagram]], saying: "He who is not sad in this time is either not a human being, or not in this world."<ref>https://www.iranintl.com/202602041011</ref>

